title: "Goosebumps" Wins the Weekend Box Office
text:
"Goosebumps" Wins the Weekend Box Office Posted today at 11:30am 
Sony/Columbia (LOS ANGELES) -- Goosebumps has bumped The Martian out of the top spot at the box office. 
The Jack Black movie, based on the book series by author R.L. Stine, earned an estimated 23.5 million dollars over the weekend to open in first place. 
The Martian , which had been number one the previous two weekends, was the runner-up this time around, collecting 21.5 million dollars. 
The Steven Spielberg-directed thriller Bridge of Spies , starring Tom Hanks, rounded out the top three, with a 15.4-million-dollar debut. 
Guillermo del Toro's horror flick, Crimson Peak , landed in fourth place, raising 12.8 million bucks in its first three days of release. 
The football drama Woodlawn made 4.1 million to open in ninth place. 
Here are the top 10 movies from Friday through Sunday, with estimated ticket sales, according to Rentrak: 
1. Goosebumps , $23.5 million2. The Martian , $21.5 million3. Bridge of Spies , $15.4 million4. Crimson Peak , $12.8 million5. Hotel Transylvania 2 , $12.3 million6. Pan , $5.9 million7. The Intern , $5.4 million8. Sicario , $4.5 million10. Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials , $2.8 million
